                            <comment id="32006" author="springboy" created="Tue, 12 Feb 2008 18:38:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Martin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WILD DIGRESSION: this is a question/coment on the issue that is orthogonal to fixing your issue &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why are you mocking the JdbcTemplate in the tests for your DAO? One rather cavalier fix for the issue would simply be to delete all of your unit tests for your DAOs &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I never write unit tests for my DAOs and thus have never run into the issue. I dispense with unit tests for my DAOs and go straight to itnegration/system tests, for the reason that stubbing (not mocking) SQL/HQL/EQL queries and so forth is not worth the effort. I&apos;m not being antagonistic here &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I&apos;m really rather just interested in knowing what value unit tests for yor DAOs brings to the table. (Your issue description doesn&apos;t explicitly mention unit tests, but mocking - stubbing - is a technique generally used in unit tests as opposed to integration tests.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now maybe for consistency there should be a setter method for the SimpleJdbcTemplate on the SimpleJdbcDaoSupport class, but that is by the by and one for Juergen.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Juergen: sorry for intruding on your space to have a discussion. I know there&apos;s a forum for this &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Haha.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
